        { "id": "d", "text": "To return a string representation" }
      ],
      "correctOptionId": "b",
      "explanation": "`__init__` is the constructor method in Python. It is automatically called when a new object (instance) of a class is created."
    },
    {
      "id": "q6",
      "text": "What is the output of the following code?",
      "codeSnippet": {
        "language": "python",
        "code": "a = [1, 2, 3]\nb = a\nc = [1, 2, 3]\nprint(a is b, a is c)"
      },
      "options": [
        { "id": "a", "text": "True True" },
        { "id": "b", "text": "True False" },
        { "id": "c", "text": "False True" },
        { "id": "d", "text": "False False" }
      ],
      "correctOptionId": "b",
      "explanation": "`a` and `b` point to the same object in memory, so `a is b` is True. `c` is a new list with the same content, but a different object in memory, so `a is c` is False."
